<TITLE> WFP to feed 2.2 mln Sidr survivors </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 29 (bdnews24.com)The World Food Programme will feed 22 lakh (2.2 million) cyclone-hit people for six months to prevent malnutrition, the UN body said in a statement Thursday. The WFP announced the plan following the latest UN survey that estimates 22 lakh people are in need of immediate food assistance in the 15 districts that were worst-hit by Cyclone Sidr on Nov 15. "The operation, at a cost of US $52 million, will provide immediate relief assistance to over 2.2 million affected people and help them restore livelihoods and rural community infrastructures," the statement said. The UN body will provide food rations consisting of rice, pulses, edible oil, blended foods, salt and high energy biscuits. The organisation has established an operational hub in Jessore and will open two field offices in Bagerhat and Barisal to deliver timely food relief for affected families, the release added. bdn
